CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 19, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "1439 'Hits' Monday - ...Plenty of Room - Terrace Village residents were slow in utilizing bus transportation owning to uncertainty of schedule. Hilltoppers decided to make sure buses would run both ways for they attempted to leave their Government Project homes.  Trolleys and buses are still running but service is slow due to inadequate number of vehicles in operation. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Girl holding bag and wearing dark coat, walking beside no. 365 bus with sign reading "Terrace - 2," at Terrace Village housing project
